    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-03-05T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-03-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="419"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.3715/30: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-05T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 5, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>276. Your X–527, March 4, 1 p.m. We have informed Cuban Chargé d’Affaires in
                    Washington that we cannot undertake to evacuate Spanish refugees but will
                    consider possibility of evacuating Cubans. You may similarly inform
                    representative of Cuban Embassy in Valencia. In view of danger to our vessels we
                    would wish to make as few trips as possible. Inquire of appropriate Spanish
                    authorities, therefore, whether they would permit as many as 100 Cuban <pb
                        facs="0498" n="486" xml:id="pg_486"/> refugees from Madrid to be assembled
                    and evacuated from Valencia at one time. Inquire also whether arrangements could
                    be made to have the examination of these refugees by Spanish officials completed
                    sufficiently in advance to permit of the departure of our naval vessel from
                    Valencia as early as 7 a.m., since we should very much prefer to carry out any
                    evacuation during daylight hours in view of danger from drifting mines.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
